CSE 3118 Assignment 1

Write an embedded C program for the AT89X51 (8051) microcontroller to control an LED using
timers, counters and interrupts. You must simulate the circuit in Proteus and write the code in
Keil.
Hardware connections:
● LED connected to P1.0
● Logicstate switch connected to INT1 (P3.3)
Requirements:
1. Timer 0 Operation
Configure Timer 0 in Mode 1 (16-bit timer mode).
Set the timer to generate approximately ## ms overflow interrupts.
Use a counter variable inside the Timer 0 ISR to create longer delays.
2. Student-Specific Delay (Mandatory)
Let ## be the last two digits of your Student ID.
The LED toggle delay must be:
Delay = ## × 10 ms
Example:
If Student ID = 20200104123, then ## = 23
LED toggle delay = 23 × 10 ms = 230 ms (## x counter variable)
The LED must automatically blink using this calculated delay. Do not use any software delay
loops. All delays must be created using the timer interrupt and counter.
3. External Interrupt 1 (INT1)
Configure External Interrupt 1 as edge-triggered.
When the push button is pressed:
● Immediately toggle the LED
● Reset the software counter variable
● Resume normal blinking
4. Counter Mode using Timer 1
Configure Timer 1 in counter mode to count external pulses (or simulated pulses in
Proteus).
After 20 counts:
● Turn the LED ON for 2 seconds

● Then return to the normal blinking operation
5. Program Constraints
● Do not use delay loops
Use only timers and interrupts
● Main function should contain an infinite loop only
● All timing must be interrupt-driven
6. Software and Simulation
● Write code in C using Keil
● Simulate the circuit in Proteus
